Pre-Game Insights: Oman's coach Duleep Mendis has seen a vast improvement in the mental aspect of his side since he took over, but his boys are still 'not hard enough' to play Test nations.
Oman has a home advantage in their bid to face off with the best in the world, as all Group B matches in the first round will be held at the Al Amerat Cricket Stadium.
Miscellaneous Highlights: PNG go into the tournament opener full of confidence, ranked three places higher than their opponents.
The PNG squad is the first group of players to represent the country at a men's World Cup, 48 years after the nation was named an associate member by the ICC.
Others: Possible Oman playing XI: Jatinder Singh, Aqib Ilyas, Ayaan Khan, Zeeshan Maqsood, Mohammad Nadeem, Sandeep Goud, Naseem Khushi, Kaleemullah, Khawar Ali, Fayyaz Butt, Bilal Khan
Possible Papua New Guinea playing XI: Assad Vala, Tony Ura, Charles Amini, Sese Bau, Norman Vanua, Simon Atai, Kiplin Doriga, Jason Kila, Nosaina Pokana, Damien Ravu, Chad Soper
